// Datasheet for the `store` device: it requires the driver to provide the components `key`/`val` and
// storage for its `Node` shape, at least 4 rows. A datasheet DESCRIBES REQUIREMENTS — it defines no
// shape; `Node` is defined by the driver (or a device impl), and `Node[4]` is a storage REQUIREMENT
// (minimum), never an allocation. The driver owns the real pool and may size it larger. Support file.
// RUN: true
key :: float;
val :: float;
[4]Node;